In platform/plugin-sdk/src/log.ts, the safeSerializeArg function (lines 31-95) handles top-level functions, symbols, and bigints at lines 42-44. But when these appear as VALUES inside an object, they go through the JSON.stringify replacer at lines 78-87. The replacer handles functions (line 83), bigints (line 84), and symbols (line 85).

Existing tests in platform/plugin-sdk/src/log.test.ts cover top-level functions (line 157), symbols (line 166), and bigints (line 174), but NOT when they appear nested inside objects. The replacer path is untested.

Add tests in the 'safe serialization' describe block. Example:

```typescript
test('serializes functions nested inside objects via JSON replacer', () => {
  const entries = collect();
  log.info('test', { callback: function myCallback() {} });
  const data = entries[0]?.data[0] as Record<string, unknown>;
  expect(data?.callback).toBe('[Function: myCallback]');
});
```

Similar tests for bigint and symbol values inside objects.

